Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Pick
@basil{1/2%ounce}(leaves picked from stems, stems discarded) and reserve a few
leaves for garnish and mince remaining. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, minced basil, lemon
zest, juice from half the lemon, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Set aside.

> Use 4 TBSP olive oil and 1 tsp salt for 4 servings.

Once water is boiling, add @orecchiette pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook until al
dente, ~{13-15%minutes}. Drain.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a
drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
chicken and season with a few large pinches of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned all over, ~{2-3%minutes}. Sprinkle with
@italian seasoning{1%teaspoon}. Continue cooking until chicken is cooked through,
~{2-3%minutes} more. Turn off heat; stir in @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}.

While chicken cooks, dice @roma tomato{1} into 1/2-inch pieces. Dice
@fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into 1/2-inch cubes.

Stir pasta, chicken, tomato, and mozzarella into #bowl{} with dressing until
everything is coated. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; divide between bowls.
Tear reserved basil leaves into pieces and sprinkle over pasta. Top with a pinch
of @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired. Slice remaining lemon into wedges and
serve on the side.